Titolo: Blitz (video game)

Anno: 1981

Descrizione: Blitz (originally Vic New York, then later New York Blitz) is an action game published by Commodore for its VIC-20 home computer in 1981. The game is based on the 1977 arcade game Canyon Bomber from Atari, Inc., replacing the goal of clearing boulders with bombing closely packed skyscrapers. Several later clones of the concept also use the city setting.
Blitz was followed by Blitz-64 for the Commodore 64 and Blitz-16 for the Commodore 16.

Genere: Non specificato


Valutazione: N/A
